cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.OS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with reducing network latency in geo-distributed deployments of transactional storage systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper leverages recent advances in network data plane programmability to execute transaction processing logic directly in network devices. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another likely category as the paper deals with transaction processing in storage systems. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to transaction processing. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also a possibility as the paper may discuss the implementation of the Gotthard system and its interaction with the operating system.
